item.title: Imposter Syndrome: Overcoming the Silent Infiltrator
item.description: Placeholder I only encountered impostor syndrome two times in my life, so far. My first experience with impostor syndrome was when I was enrolled in NWFSC’s Collegiate High School. My local community college founded a high school, believing that, with the proper support, high school students could succeed in college courses full time and gradudate with both their Associate of Arts and high school diploma. One day, I had a visceral, uncomfortable feeling in my stomach: “why am I here?
